- always follow the format used in other files
- never hardcode any color
- as all are avaiable in the theme context, use it
- use the brand color for any brand related element
- use the hover brand color for any hover brand related element

- use the background color for any background related element
- use the text color for any text related element
- use the light background color for any light background related element(these are the elements that you want lowkey like dont want them to take full focus of the user)
- from now on dont use the tint color for any element
- if for hover the color is not available in the theme context, use the hoverbrand color hardcoded
- for brand colors the hover should be brandHover
- for text the hover should be textHover